115  /** Determines whether a `thing` is an object for the purposes of RSJF. In this case, `thing` is an object if it has
116   * the type `object` but is NOT null, an array or a File.
117   *
118   * @param thing - The thing to check to see whether it is an object
119   * @returns - True if it is a non-null, non-array, non-File object
120   */
121  function isObject(thing) {
122      if (typeof File !== 'undefined' && thing instanceof File) {
123          return false;
124      }
125      if (typeof Date !== 'undefined' && thing instanceof Date) {
126          return false;
127      }
128      return typeof thing === 'object' && thing !== null && !Array.isArray(thing);
129  }

133  /** Checks the schema to see if it is allowing additional items, by verifying that `schema.additionalItems` is an
134   * object. The user is warned in the console if `schema.additionalItems` has the value `true`.
135   *
136   * @param schema - The schema object to check
137   * @returns - True if additional items is allowed, otherwise false
138   */
139  function allowAdditionalItems(schema) {
140      if (schema.additionalItems === true) {
141          console.warn('additionalItems=true is currently not supported');
142      }
143      return isObject(schema.additionalItems);
144  }

147  /** Attempts to convert the string into a number. If an empty string is provided, then `undefined` is returned. If a
148   * `null` is provided, it is returned. If the string ends in a `.` then the string is returned because the user may be
149   * in the middle of typing a float number. If a number ends in a pattern like `.0`, `.20`, `.030`, string is returned
150   * because the user may be typing number that will end in a non-zero digit. Otherwise, the string is wrapped by
151   * `Number()` and if that result is not `NaN`, that number will be returned, otherwise the string `value` will be.
152   *
153   * @param value - The string or null value to convert to a number
154   * @returns - The `value` converted to a number when appropriate, otherwise the `value`
155   */
156  function asNumber(value) {
157      if (value === '') {
158          return undefined;
159      }
160      if (value === null) {
161          return null;
162      }
163      if (/\.$/.test(value)) {
164          // '3.' can't really be considered a number even if it parses in js. The
165          // user is most likely entering a float.
166          return value;
167      }
168      if (/\.0$/.test(value)) {
169          // we need to return this as a string here, to allow for input like 3.07
170          return value;
171      }
172      if (/\.\d*0$/.test(value)) {
173          // It's a number, that's cool - but we need it as a string so it doesn't screw
174          // with the user when entering dollar amounts or other values (such as those with
175          // specific precision or number of significant digits)
176          return value;
177      }
178      const n = Number(value);
179      const valid = typeof n === 'number' && !Number.isNaN(n);
180      return valid ? n : value;
181  }

219  /** Get all passed options from ui:options, and ui:<optionName>, returning them in an object with the `ui:`
220   * stripped off. Any `globalOptions` will always be returned, unless they are overridden by options in the `uiSchema`.
221   *
222   * @param [uiSchema={}] - The UI Schema from which to get any `ui:xxx` options
223   * @param [globalOptions={}] - The optional Global UI Schema from which to get any fallback `xxx` options
224   * @returns - An object containing all the `ui:xxx` options with the `ui:` stripped off along with all `globalOptions`
225   */
226  function getUiOptions(uiSchema = {}, globalOptions = {}) {
227      return Object.keys(uiSchema)
228          .filter((key) => key.indexOf('ui:') === 0)
229          .reduce((options, key) => {
230          const value = uiSchema[key];
231          if (key === UI_WIDGET_KEY && isObject(value)) {
232              console.error('Setting options via ui:widget object is no longer supported, use ui:options instead');
233              return options;
234          }
235          if (key === UI_OPTIONS_KEY && isObject(value)) {
236              return { ...options, ...value };
237          }
238          return { ...options, [key.substring(3)]: value };
239      }, { ...globalOptions });
240  }

244  /** Checks whether the field described by `schema`, having the `uiSchema` and `formData` supports expanding. The UI for
245   * the field can expand if it has additional properties, is not forced as non-expandable by the `uiSchema` and the
246   * `formData` object doesn't already have `schema.maxProperties` elements.
247   *
248   * @param schema - The schema for the field that is being checked
249   * @param [uiSchema={}] - The uiSchema for the field
250   * @param [formData] - The formData for the field
251   * @returns - True if the schema element has additionalProperties, is expandable, and not at the maxProperties limit
252   */
253  function canExpand(schema, uiSchema = {}, formData) {
254      if (!schema.additionalProperties) {
255          return false;
256      }
257      const { expandable = true } = getUiOptions(uiSchema);
258      if (expandable === false) {
259          return expandable;
260      }
261      // if ui:options.expandable was not explicitly set to false, we can add
262      // another property if we have not exceeded maxProperties yet
263      if (schema.maxProperties !== undefined && formData) {
264          return Object.keys(formData).length < schema.maxProperties;
265      }
266      return true;
267  }

275  /** Given a `formData` object, recursively creates a `FormValidation` error handling structure around it
276   *
277   * @param formData - The form data around which the error handler is created
278   * @returns - A `FormValidation` object based on the `formData` structure
279   */
280  function createErrorHandler(formData) {
281      const handler = {
282          // We store the list of errors for this node in a property named __errors
283          // to avoid name collision with a possible sub schema field named
284          // 'errors' (see `utils.toErrorSchema`).
285          [ERRORS_KEY]: [],
286          addError(message) {
287              this[ERRORS_KEY].push(message);
288          },
289      };
290      if (Array.isArray(formData)) {
291          return formData.reduce((acc, value, key) => {
292              return { ...acc, [key]: createErrorHandler(value) };
293          }, handler);
294      }
295      if (isPlainObject_default()(formData)) {
296          const formObject = formData;
297          return Object.keys(formObject).reduce((acc, key) => {
298              return { ...acc, [key]: createErrorHandler(formObject[key]) };
299          }, handler);
300      }
301      return handler;
302  }

309  /** Implements a deep equals using the `lodash.isEqualWith` function, that provides a customized comparator that
310   * assumes all functions are equivalent.
311   *
312   * @param a - The first element to compare
313   * @param b - The second element to compare
314   * @returns - True if the `a` and `b` are deeply equal, false otherwise
315   */
316  function deepEquals(a, b) {
317      return isEqualWith_default()(a, b, (obj, other) => {
318          if (typeof obj === 'function' && typeof other === 'function') {
319              // Assume all functions are equivalent
320              // see https://github.com/rjsf-team/react-jsonschema-form/issues/255
321              return true;
322          }
323          return undefined; // fallback to default isEquals behavior
324      });
325  }

342  /** Splits out the value at the `key` in `object` from the `object`, returning an array that contains in the first
343   * location, the `object` minus the `key: value` and in the second location the `value`.
344   *
345   * @param key - The key from the object to extract
346   * @param object - The object from which to extract the element
347   * @returns - An array with the first value being the object minus the `key` element and the second element being the
348   *      value from `object[key]`
349   */
350  function splitKeyElementFromObject(key, object) {
351      const value = object[key];
352      const remaining = omit_default()(object, [key]);
353      return [remaining, value];
354  }
355  /** Given the name of a `$ref` from within a schema, using the `rootSchema`, look up and return the sub-schema using the
356   * path provided by that reference. If `#` is not the first character of the reference, or the path does not exist in
357   * the schema, then throw an Error. Otherwise return the sub-schema. Also deals with nested `$ref`s in the sub-schema.
358   *
359   * @param $ref - The ref string for which the schema definition is desired
360   * @param [rootSchema={}] - The root schema in which to search for the definition
361   * @returns - The sub-schema within the `rootSchema` which matches the `$ref` if it exists
362   * @throws - Error indicating that no schema for that reference exists
363   */
364  function findSchemaDefinition($ref, rootSchema = {}) {
365      let ref = $ref || '';
366      if (ref.startsWith('#')) {
367          // Decode URI fragment representation.
368          ref = decodeURIComponent(ref.substring(1));
369      }
370      else {
371          throw new Error(`Could not find a definition for ${$ref}.`);
372      }
373      const current = jsonpointer.get(rootSchema, ref);
374      if (current === undefined) {
375          throw new Error(`Could not find a definition for ${$ref}.`);
376      }
377      if (current[REF_KEY]) {
378          const [remaining, theRef] = splitKeyElementFromObject(REF_KEY, current);
379          const subSchema = findSchemaDefinition(theRef, rootSchema);
380          if (Object.keys(remaining).length > 0) {
381              return { ...remaining, ...subSchema };
382          }
383          return subSchema;
384      }
385      return current;
386  }

409  /** Compares the value of `discriminatorField` within `formData` against the value of `discriminatorField` within schema for each `option`.
410   * Returns index of first `option` whose discriminator matches formData. Returns `undefined` if there is no match.
411   * This function does not work with discriminators of `"type": "object"` and `"type": "array"`
412   *
413   * @param formData - The current formData, if any, used to figure out a match
414   * @param options - The list of options to find a matching options from
415   * @param [discriminatorField] - The optional name of the field within the options object whose value is used to
416   *          determine which option is selected
417   * @returns - The index of the matched option or undefined if there is no match
418   */
419  function getOptionMatchingSimpleDiscriminator(formData, options, discriminatorField) {
420      var _a;
421      if (formData && discriminatorField) {
422          const value = get_default()(formData, discriminatorField);
423          if (value === undefined) {
424              return;
425          }
426          for (let i = 0; i < options.length; i++) {
427              const option = options[i];
428              const discriminator = get_default()(option, [PROPERTIES_KEY, discriminatorField], {});
429              if (discriminator.type === 'object' || discriminator.type === 'array') {
430                  continue;
431              }
432              if (discriminator.const === value) {
433                  return i;
434              }
435              if ((_a = discriminator.enum) === null || _a === void 0 ? void 0 : _a.includes(value)) {
436                  return i;
437              }
438          }
439      }
440      return;
441  }

449  /** Given the `formData` and list of `options`, attempts to find the index of the option that best matches the data.
450   * Deprecated, use `getFirstMatchingOption()` instead.
451   *
452   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used when necessary
453   * @param formData - The current formData, if any, used to figure out a match
454   * @param options - The list of options to find a matching options from
455   * @param rootSchema - The root schema, used to primarily to look up `$ref`s
456   * @param [discriminatorField] - The optional name of the field within the options object whose value is used to
457   *          determine which option is selected
458   * @returns - The index of the matched option or 0 if none is available
459   * @deprecated
460   */
461  function getMatchingOption(validator, formData, options, rootSchema, discriminatorField) {
462      // For performance, skip validating subschemas if formData is undefined. We just
463      // want to get the first option in that case.
464      if (formData === undefined) {
465          return 0;
466      }
467      const simpleDiscriminatorMatch = getOptionMatchingSimpleDiscriminator(formData, options, discriminatorField);
468      if (isNumber_default()(simpleDiscriminatorMatch)) {
469          return simpleDiscriminatorMatch;
470      }
471      for (let i = 0; i < options.length; i++) {
472          const option = options[i];
473          // If we have a discriminator field, then we will use this to make the determination
474          if (discriminatorField && has_default()(option, [PROPERTIES_KEY, discriminatorField])) {
475              const value = get_default()(formData, discriminatorField);
476              const discriminator = get_default()(option, [PROPERTIES_KEY, discriminatorField], {});
477              if (validator.isValid(discriminator, value, rootSchema)) {
478                  return i;
479              }
480          }
481          else if (option[PROPERTIES_KEY]) {
482              // If the schema describes an object then we need to add slightly more
483              // strict matching to the schema, because unless the schema uses the
484              // "requires" keyword, an object will match the schema as long as it
485              // doesn't have matching keys with a conflicting type. To do this we use an
486              // "anyOf" with an array of requires. This augmentation expresses that the
487              // schema should match if any of the keys in the schema are present on the
488              // object and pass validation.
489              //
490              // Create an "anyOf" schema that requires at least one of the keys in the
491              // "properties" object
492              const requiresAnyOf = {
493                  anyOf: Object.keys(option[PROPERTIES_KEY]).map((key) => ({
494                      required: [key],
495                  })),
496              };
497              let augmentedSchema;
498              // If the "anyOf" keyword already exists, wrap the augmentation in an "allOf"
499              if (option.anyOf) {
500                  // Create a shallow clone of the option
501                  const { ...shallowClone } = option;
502                  if (!shallowClone.allOf) {
503                      shallowClone.allOf = [];
504                  }
505                  else {
506                      // If "allOf" already exists, shallow clone the array
507                      shallowClone.allOf = shallowClone.allOf.slice();
508                  }
509                  shallowClone.allOf.push(requiresAnyOf);
510                  augmentedSchema = shallowClone;
511              }
512              else {
513                  augmentedSchema = Object.assign({}, option, requiresAnyOf);
514              }
515              // Remove the "required" field as it's likely that not all fields have
516              // been filled in yet, which will mean that the schema is not valid
517              delete augmentedSchema.required;
518              if (validator.isValid(augmentedSchema, formData, rootSchema)) {
519                  return i;
520              }
521          }
522          else if (validator.isValid(option, formData, rootSchema)) {
523              return i;
524          }
525      }
526      return 0;
527  }

589  /** Given a specific `value` attempts to guess the type of a schema element. In the case where we have to implicitly
590   *  create a schema, it is useful to know what type to use based on the data we are defining.
591   *
592   * @param value - The value from which to guess the type
593   * @returns - The best guess for the object type
594   */
595  function guessType(value) {
596      if (Array.isArray(value)) {
597          return 'array';
598      }
599      if (typeof value === 'string') {
600          return 'string';
601      }
602      if (value == null) {
603          return 'null';
604      }
605      if (typeof value === 'boolean') {
606          return 'boolean';
607      }
608      if (!isNaN(value)) {
609          return 'number';
610      }
611      if (typeof value === 'object') {
612          return 'object';
613      }
614      // Default to string if we can't figure it out
615      return 'string';
616  }
617  //# sourceMappingURL=guessType.js.map

621  ;// CONCATENATED MODULE: ../node_modules/@rjsf/utils/lib/getSchemaType.js
622  
623  /** Gets the type of a given `schema`. If the type is not explicitly defined, then an attempt is made to infer it from
624   * other elements of the schema as follows:
625   * - schema.const: Returns the `guessType()` of that value
626   * - schema.enum: Returns `string`
627   * - schema.properties: Returns `object`
628   * - schema.additionalProperties: Returns `object`
629   * - type is an array with a length of 2 and one type is 'null': Returns the other type
630   *
631   * @param schema - The schema for which to get the type
632   * @returns - The type of the schema
633   */
634  function getSchemaType(schema) {
635      let { type } = schema;
636      if (!type && schema.const) {
637          return guessType(schema.const);
638      }
639      if (!type && schema.enum) {
640          return 'string';
641      }
642      if (!type && (schema.properties || schema.additionalProperties)) {
643          return 'object';
644      }
645      if (Array.isArray(type)) {
646          if (type.length === 2 && type.includes('null')) {
647              type = type.find((type) => type !== 'null');
648          }
649          else {
650              type = type[0];
651          }
652      }
653      return type;
654  }

661  /** Recursively merge deeply nested schemas. The difference between `mergeSchemas` and `mergeObjects` is that
662   * `mergeSchemas` only concats arrays for values under the 'required' keyword, and when it does, it doesn't include
663   * duplicate values.
664   *
665   * @param obj1 - The first schema object to merge
666   * @param obj2 - The second schema object to merge
667   * @returns - The merged schema object
668   */
669  function mergeSchemas(obj1, obj2) {
670      const acc = Object.assign({}, obj1); // Prevent mutation of source object.
671      return Object.keys(obj2).reduce((acc, key) => {
672          const left = obj1 ? obj1[key] : {}, right = obj2[key];
673          if (obj1 && key in obj1 && isObject(right)) {
674              acc[key] = mergeSchemas(left, right);
675          }
676          else if (obj1 &&
677              obj2 &&
678              (getSchemaType(obj1) === 'object' || getSchemaType(obj2) === 'object') &&
679              key === REQUIRED_KEY &&
680              Array.isArray(left) &&
681              Array.isArray(right)) {
682              // Don't include duplicate values when merging 'required' fields.
683              acc[key] = union_default()(left, right);
684          }
685          else {
686              acc[key] = right;
687          }
688          return acc;
689      }, acc);
690  }

709  /** Retrieves an expanded schema that has had all of its conditions, additional properties, references and dependencies
710   * resolved and merged into the `schema` given a `validator`, `rootSchema` and `rawFormData` that is used to do the
711   * potentially recursive resolution.
712   *
713   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
714   * @param schema - The schema for which retrieving a schema is desired
715   * @param [rootSchema={}] - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
716   * @param [rawFormData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
717   * @returns - The schema having its conditions, additional properties, references and dependencies resolved
718   */
719  function retrieveSchema(validator, schema, rootSchema = {}, rawFormData) {
720      return retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, schema, rootSchema, rawFormData)[0];
721  }
722  /** Resolves a conditional block (if/else/then) by removing the condition and merging the appropriate conditional branch
723   * with the rest of the schema. If `expandAllBranches` is true, then the `retrieveSchemaInteral()` results for both
724   * conditions will be returned.
725   *
726   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that is used to detect valid schema conditions
727   * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a condition is desired
728   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
729   * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and
730   *          dependencies as a list of schemas
731   * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
732   * @param [formData] - The current formData to assist retrieving a schema
733   * @returns - A list of schemas with the appropriate conditions resolved, possibly with all branches expanded
734   */
735  function resolveCondition(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
736      const { if: expression, then, else: otherwise, ...resolvedSchemaLessConditional } = schema;
737      const conditionValue = validator.isValid(expression, formData || {}, rootSchema);
738      let resolvedSchemas = [resolvedSchemaLessConditional];
739      let schemas = [];
740      if (expandAllBranches) {
741          if (then && typeof then !== 'boolean') {
742              schemas = schemas.concat(retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, then, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList));
743          }
744          if (otherwise && typeof otherwise !== 'boolean') {
745              schemas = schemas.concat(retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, otherwise, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList));
746          }
747      }
748      else {
749          const conditionalSchema = conditionValue ? then : otherwise;
750          if (conditionalSchema && typeof conditionalSchema !== 'boolean') {
751              schemas = schemas.concat(retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, conditionalSchema, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList));
752          }
753      }
754      if (schemas.length) {
755          resolvedSchemas = schemas.map((s) => mergeSchemas(resolvedSchemaLessConditional, s));
756      }
757      return resolvedSchemas.flatMap((s) => retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, s, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList));
758  }
759  /** Given a list of lists of allOf, anyOf or oneOf values, create a list of lists of all permutations of the values. The
760   * `listOfLists` is expected to be all resolved values of the 1st...nth schemas within an `allOf`, `anyOf` or `oneOf`.
761   * From those lists, build a matrix for each `xxxOf` where there is more than one schema for a row in the list of lists.
762   *
763   * For example:
764   * - If there are three xxxOf rows (A, B, C) and they have been resolved such that there is only one A, two B and three
765   *   C schemas then:
766   *   - The permutation for the first row is `[[A]]`
767   *   - The permutations for the second row are `[[A,B1], [A,B2]]`
768   *   - The permutations for the third row are `[[A,B1,C1], [A,B1,C2], [A,B1,C3], [A,B2,C1], [A,B2,C2], [A,B2,C3]]`
769   *
770   * @param listOfLists - The list of lists of elements that represent the allOf, anyOf or oneOf resolved values in order
771   * @returns - The list of all permutations of schemas for a set of `xxxOf`s
772   */
773  function getAllPermutationsOfXxxOf(listOfLists) {
774      const allPermutations = listOfLists.reduce((permutations, list) => {
775          // When there are more than one set of schemas for a row, duplicate the set of permutations and add in the values
776          if (list.length > 1) {
777              return list.flatMap((element) => times_default()(permutations.length, (i) => [...permutations[i]].concat(element)));
778          }
779          // Otherwise just push in the single value into the current set of permutations
780          permutations.forEach((permutation) => permutation.push(list[0]));
781          return permutations;
782      }, [[]] // Start with an empty list
783      );
784      return allPermutations;
785  }
786  /** Resolves references and dependencies within a schema and its 'allOf' children. Passes the `expandAllBranches` flag
787   * down to the `retrieveSchemaInternal()`, `resolveReference()` and `resolveDependencies()` helper calls. If
788   * `expandAllBranches` is true, then all possible dependencies and/or allOf branches are returned.
789   *
790   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
791   * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a schema is desired
792   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
793   * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
794   *          as a list of schemas
795   * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
796   * @param [formData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
797   * @returns - The list of schemas having its references, dependencies and allOf schemas resolved
798   */
799  function resolveSchema(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
800      const updatedSchemas = resolveReference(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData);
801      if (updatedSchemas.length > 1 || updatedSchemas[0] !== schema) {
802          // return the updatedSchemas array if it has either multiple schemas within it
803          // OR the first schema is not the same as the original schema
804          return updatedSchemas;
805      }
806      if (DEPENDENCIES_KEY in schema) {
807          const resolvedSchemas = resolveDependencies(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData);
808          return resolvedSchemas.flatMap((s) => {
809              return retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, s, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList);
810          });
811      }
812      if (ALL_OF_KEY in schema && Array.isArray(schema.allOf)) {
813          const allOfSchemaElements = schema.allOf.map((allOfSubschema) => retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, allOfSubschema, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList));
814          const allPermutations = getAllPermutationsOfXxxOf(allOfSchemaElements);
815          return allPermutations.map((permutation) => ({ ...schema, allOf: permutation }));
816      }
817      // No $ref or dependencies or allOf attribute was found, returning the original schema.
818      return [schema];
819  }
820  /** Resolves all references within a schema and then returns the `retrieveSchemaInternal()` if the resolved schema is
821   * actually different than the original. Passes the `expandAllBranches` flag down to the `retrieveSchemaInternal()`
822   * helper call.
823   *
824   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
825   * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a reference is desired
826   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
827   * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
828   *          as a list of schemas
829   * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
830   * @param [formData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
831   * @returns - The list schemas retrieved after having all references resolved
832   */
833  function resolveReference(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
834      const updatedSchema = resolveAllReferences(schema, rootSchema, recurseList);
835      if (updatedSchema !== schema) {
836          // Only call this if the schema was actually changed by the `resolveAllReferences()` function
837          return retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, updatedSchema, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList);
838      }
839      return [schema];
840  }
841  /** Resolves all references within the schema itself as well as any of its properties and array items.
842   *
843   * @param schema - The schema for which resolving all references is desired
844   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
845   * @param recurseList - List of $refs already resolved to prevent recursion
846   * @returns - given schema will all references resolved or the original schema if no internal `$refs` were resolved
847   */
848  function resolveAllReferences(schema, rootSchema, recurseList) {
849      if (!isObject(schema)) {
850          return schema;
851      }
852      let resolvedSchema = schema;
853      // resolve top level ref
854      if (REF_KEY in resolvedSchema) {
855          const { $ref, ...localSchema } = resolvedSchema;
856          // Check for a recursive reference and stop the loop
857          if (recurseList.includes($ref)) {
858              return resolvedSchema;
859          }
860          recurseList.push($ref);
861          // Retrieve the referenced schema definition.
862          const refSchema = findSchemaDefinition($ref, rootSchema);
863          resolvedSchema = { ...refSchema, ...localSchema };
864      }
865      if (PROPERTIES_KEY in resolvedSchema) {
866          const childrenLists = [];
867          const updatedProps = transform_default()(resolvedSchema[PROPERTIES_KEY], (result, value, key) => {
868              const childList = [...recurseList];
869              result[key] = resolveAllReferences(value, rootSchema, childList);
870              childrenLists.push(childList);
871          }, {});
872          merge_default()(recurseList, uniq_default()(flattenDeep_default()(childrenLists)));
873          resolvedSchema = { ...resolvedSchema, [PROPERTIES_KEY]: updatedProps };
874      }
875      if (ITEMS_KEY in resolvedSchema &&
876          !Array.isArray(resolvedSchema.items) &&
877          typeof resolvedSchema.items !== 'boolean') {
878          resolvedSchema = {
879              ...resolvedSchema,
880              items: resolveAllReferences(resolvedSchema.items, rootSchema, recurseList),
881          };
882      }
883      return isEqual_default()(schema, resolvedSchema) ? schema : resolvedSchema;
884  }
885  /** Creates new 'properties' items for each key in the `formData`
886   *
887   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used when necessary
888   * @param theSchema - The schema for which the existing additional properties is desired
889   * @param [rootSchema] - The root schema, used to primarily to look up `$ref`s * @param validator
890   * @param [aFormData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
891   * @returns - The updated schema with additional properties stubbed
892   */
893  function stubExistingAdditionalProperties(validator, theSchema, rootSchema, aFormData) {
894      // Clone the schema so that we don't ruin the consumer's original
895      const schema = {
896          ...theSchema,
897          properties: { ...theSchema.properties },
898      };
899      // make sure formData is an object
900      const formData = aFormData && isObject(aFormData) ? aFormData : {};
901      Object.keys(formData).forEach((key) => {
902          if (key in schema.properties) {
903              // No need to stub, our schema already has the property
904              return;
905          }
906          let additionalProperties = {};
907          if (typeof schema.additionalProperties !== 'boolean') {
908              if (REF_KEY in schema.additionalProperties) {
909                  additionalProperties = retrieveSchema(validator, { $ref: get_default()(schema.additionalProperties, [REF_KEY]) }, rootSchema, formData);
910              }
911              else if ('type' in schema.additionalProperties) {
912                  additionalProperties = { ...schema.additionalProperties };
913              }
914              else if (ANY_OF_KEY in schema.additionalProperties || ONE_OF_KEY in schema.additionalProperties) {
915                  additionalProperties = {
916                      type: 'object',
917                      ...schema.additionalProperties,
918                  };
919              }
920              else {
921                  additionalProperties = { type: guessType(get_default()(formData, [key])) };
922              }
923          }
924          else {
925              additionalProperties = { type: guessType(get_default()(formData, [key])) };
926          }
927          // The type of our new key should match the additionalProperties value;
928          schema.properties[key] = additionalProperties;
929          // Set our additional property flag so we know it was dynamically added
930          set_default()(schema.properties, [key, ADDITIONAL_PROPERTY_FLAG], true);
931      });
932      return schema;
933  }
934  /** Internal handler that retrieves an expanded schema that has had all of its conditions, additional properties,
935   * references and dependencies resolved and merged into the `schema` given a `validator`, `rootSchema` and `rawFormData`
936   * that is used to do the potentially recursive resolution. If `expandAllBranches` is true, then all possible branches
937   * of the schema and its references, conditions and dependencies are returned.
938   *
939   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
940   * @param schema - The schema for which retrieving a schema is desired
941   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
942   * @param [rawFormData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
943   * @param [expandAllBranches=false] - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and
944   *          dependencies as a list of schemas
945   * @param [recurseList=[]] - The optional, list of recursive references already processed
946   * @returns - The schema(s) resulting from having its conditions, additional properties, references and dependencies
947   *          resolved. Multiple schemas may be returned if `expandAllBranches` is true.
948   */
949  function retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, schema, rootSchema, rawFormData, expandAllBranches = false, recurseList = []) {
950      if (!isObject(schema)) {
951          return [{}];
952      }
953      const resolvedSchemas = resolveSchema(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, rawFormData);
954      return resolvedSchemas.flatMap((s) => {
955          let resolvedSchema = s;
956          if (IF_KEY in resolvedSchema) {
957              return resolveCondition(validator, resolvedSchema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, rawFormData);
958          }
959          if (ALL_OF_KEY in resolvedSchema) {
960              // resolve allOf schemas
961              if (expandAllBranches) {
962                  const { allOf, ...restOfSchema } = resolvedSchema;
963                  return [...allOf, restOfSchema];
964              }
965              try {
966                  resolvedSchema = src_default()(resolvedSchema, {
967                      deep: false,
968                  });
969              }
970              catch (e) {
971                  console.warn('could not merge subschemas in allOf:\n', e);
972                  const { allOf, ...resolvedSchemaWithoutAllOf } = resolvedSchema;
973                  return resolvedSchemaWithoutAllOf;
974              }
975          }
976          const hasAdditionalProperties = ADDITIONAL_PROPERTIES_KEY in resolvedSchema && resolvedSchema.additionalProperties !== false;
977          if (hasAdditionalProperties) {
978              return stubExistingAdditionalProperties(validator, resolvedSchema, rootSchema, rawFormData);
979          }
980          return resolvedSchema;
981      });
982  }
983  /** Resolves an `anyOf` or `oneOf` within a schema (if present) to the list of schemas returned from
984   * `retrieveSchemaInternal()` for the best matching option. If `expandAllBranches` is true, then a list of schemas for ALL
985   * options are retrieved and returned.
986   *
987   * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
988   * @param schema - The schema for which retrieving a schema is desired
989   * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
990   * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
991   *          as a list of schemas
992   * @param [rawFormData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema, defaults to an empty object
993   * @returns - Either an array containing the best matching option or all options if `expandAllBranches` is true
994   */
995  function resolveAnyOrOneOfSchemas(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, rawFormData) {
996      let anyOrOneOf;
997      const { oneOf, anyOf, ...remaining } = schema;
998      if (Array.isArray(oneOf)) {
999          anyOrOneOf = oneOf;
1000     }
1001     else if (Array.isArray(anyOf)) {
1002         anyOrOneOf = anyOf;
1003     }
1004     if (anyOrOneOf) {
1005         // Ensure that during expand all branches we pass an object rather than undefined so that all options are interrogated
1006         const formData = rawFormData === undefined && expandAllBranches ? {} : rawFormData;
1007         const discriminator = getDiscriminatorFieldFromSchema(schema);
1008         anyOrOneOf = anyOrOneOf.map((s) => {
1009             // Due to anyOf/oneOf possibly using the same $ref we always pass a fresh recurse list array so that each option
1010             // can resolve recursive references independently
1011             return resolveAllReferences(s, rootSchema, []);
1012         });
1013         // Call this to trigger the set of isValid() calls that the schema parser will need
1014         const option = getFirstMatchingOption(validator, formData, anyOrOneOf, rootSchema, discriminator);
1015         if (expandAllBranches) {
1016             return anyOrOneOf.map((item) => mergeSchemas(remaining, item));
1017         }
1018         schema = mergeSchemas(remaining, anyOrOneOf[option]);
1019     }
1020     return [schema];
1021 }
1022 /** Resolves dependencies within a schema and its 'anyOf/oneOf' children. Passes the `expandAllBranches` flag down to
1023  * the `resolveAnyOrOneOfSchema()` and `processDependencies()` helper calls.
1024  *
1025  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1026  * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a dependency is desired
1027  * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1028  * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
1029  *          as a list of schemas
1030  * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
1031  * @param [formData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
1032  * @returns - The list of schemas with their dependencies resolved
1033  */
1034 function resolveDependencies(validator, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
1035     // Drop the dependencies from the source schema.
1036     const { dependencies, ...remainingSchema } = schema;
1037     const resolvedSchemas = resolveAnyOrOneOfSchemas(validator, remainingSchema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, formData);
1038     return resolvedSchemas.flatMap((resolvedSchema) => processDependencies(validator, dependencies, resolvedSchema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData));
1039 }
1040 /** Processes all the `dependencies` recursively into the list of `resolvedSchema`s as needed. Passes the
1041  * `expandAllBranches` flag down to the `withDependentSchema()` and the recursive `processDependencies()` helper calls.
1042  *
1043  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1044  * @param dependencies - The set of dependencies that needs to be processed
1045  * @param resolvedSchema - The schema for which processing dependencies is desired
1046  * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1047  * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
1048  *          as a list of schemas
1049  * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
1050  * @param [formData] - The current formData, if any, to assist retrieving a schema
1051  * @returns - The schema with the `dependencies` resolved into it
1052  */
1053 function processDependencies(validator, dependencies, resolvedSchema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
1054     let schemas = [resolvedSchema];
1055     // Process dependencies updating the local schema properties as appropriate.
1056     for (const dependencyKey in dependencies) {
1057         // Skip this dependency if its trigger property is not present.
1058         if (!expandAllBranches && get_default()(formData, [dependencyKey]) === undefined) {
1059             continue;
1060         }
1061         // Skip this dependency if it is not included in the schema (such as when dependencyKey is itself a hidden dependency.)
1062         if (resolvedSchema.properties && !(dependencyKey in resolvedSchema.properties)) {
1063             continue;
1064         }
1065         const [remainingDependencies, dependencyValue] = splitKeyElementFromObject(dependencyKey, dependencies);
1066         if (Array.isArray(dependencyValue)) {
1067             schemas[0] = withDependentProperties(resolvedSchema, dependencyValue);
1068         }
1069         else if (isObject(dependencyValue)) {
1070             schemas = withDependentSchema(validator, resolvedSchema, rootSchema, dependencyKey, dependencyValue, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData);
1071         }
1072         return schemas.flatMap((schema) => processDependencies(validator, remainingDependencies, schema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData));
1073     }
1074     return schemas;
1075 }
1076 /** Updates a schema with additionally required properties added
1077  *
1078  * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a dependent properties is desired
1079  * @param [additionallyRequired] - An optional array of additionally required names
1080  * @returns - The schema with the additional required values merged in
1081  */
1082 function withDependentProperties(schema, additionallyRequired) {
1083     if (!additionallyRequired) {
1084         return schema;
1085     }
1086     const required = Array.isArray(schema.required)
1087         ? Array.from(new Set([...schema.required, ...additionallyRequired]))
1088         : additionallyRequired;
1089     return { ...schema, required: required };
1090 }
1091 /** Merges a dependent schema into the `schema` dealing with oneOfs and references. Passes the `expandAllBranches` flag
1092  * down to the `retrieveSchemaInternal()`, `resolveReference()` and `withExactlyOneSubschema()` helper calls.
1093  *
1094  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1095  * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a dependent schema is desired
1096  * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1097  * @param dependencyKey - The key name of the dependency
1098  * @param dependencyValue - The potentially dependent schema
1099  * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
1100  *          as a list of schemas
1101  * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
1102  * @param [formData]- The current formData to assist retrieving a schema
1103  * @returns - The list of schemas with the dependent schema resolved into them
1104  */
1105 function withDependentSchema(validator, schema, rootSchema, dependencyKey, dependencyValue, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
1106     const dependentSchemas = retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, dependencyValue, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList);
1107     return dependentSchemas.flatMap((dependent) => {
1108         const { oneOf, ...dependentSchema } = dependent;
1109         schema = mergeSchemas(schema, dependentSchema);
1110         // Since it does not contain oneOf, we return the original schema.
1111         if (oneOf === undefined) {
1112             return schema;
1113         }
1114         // Resolve $refs inside oneOf.
1115         const resolvedOneOfs = oneOf.map((subschema) => {
1116             if (typeof subschema === 'boolean' || !(REF_KEY in subschema)) {
1117                 return [subschema];
1118             }
1119             return resolveReference(validator, subschema, rootSchema, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData);
1120         });
1121         const allPermutations = getAllPermutationsOfXxxOf(resolvedOneOfs);
1122         return allPermutations.flatMap((resolvedOneOf) => withExactlyOneSubschema(validator, schema, rootSchema, dependencyKey, resolvedOneOf, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData));
1123     });
1124 }
1125 /** Returns a list of `schema`s with the best choice from the `oneOf` options merged into it. If `expandAllBranches` is
1126  * true, then a list of schemas for ALL options are retrieved and returned. Passes the `expandAllBranches` flag down to
1127  * the `retrieveSchemaInternal()` helper call.
1128  *
1129  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used to validate oneOf options
1130  * @param schema - The schema for which resolving a oneOf subschema is desired
1131  * @param rootSchema - The root schema that will be forwarded to all the APIs
1132  * @param dependencyKey - The key name of the oneOf dependency
1133  * @param oneOf - The list of schemas representing the oneOf options
1134  * @param expandAllBranches - Flag, if true, will return all possible branches of conditions, any/oneOf and dependencies
1135  *          as a list of schemas
1136  * @param recurseList - The list of recursive references already processed
1137  * @param [formData] - The current formData to assist retrieving a schema
1138  * @returns - Either an array containing the best matching option or all options if `expandAllBranches` is true
1139  */
1140 function withExactlyOneSubschema(validator, schema, rootSchema, dependencyKey, oneOf, expandAllBranches, recurseList, formData) {
1141     const validSubschemas = oneOf.filter((subschema) => {
1142         if (typeof subschema === 'boolean' || !subschema || !subschema.properties) {
1143             return false;
1144         }
1145         const { [dependencyKey]: conditionPropertySchema } = subschema.properties;
1146         if (conditionPropertySchema) {
1147             const conditionSchema = {
1148                 type: 'object',
1149                 properties: {
1150                     [dependencyKey]: conditionPropertySchema,
1151                 },
1152             };
1153             return validator.isValid(conditionSchema, formData, rootSchema) || expandAllBranches;
1154         }
1155         return false;
1156     });
1157     if (!expandAllBranches && validSubschemas.length !== 1) {
1158         console.warn("ignoring oneOf in dependencies because there isn't exactly one subschema that is valid");
1159         return [schema];
1160     }
1161     return validSubschemas.flatMap((s) => {
1162         const subschema = s;
1163         const [dependentSubschema] = splitKeyElementFromObject(dependencyKey, subschema.properties);
1164         const dependentSchema = { ...subschema, properties: dependentSubschema };
1165         const schemas = retrieveSchemaInternal(validator, dependentSchema, rootSchema, formData, expandAllBranches, recurseList);
1166         return schemas.map((s) => mergeSchemas(schema, s));
1167     });
1168 }

1184 /** A junk option used to determine when the getFirstMatchingOption call really matches an option rather than returning
1185  * the first item
1186  */
1187 const JUNK_OPTION = {
1188     type: 'object',
1189     $id: JUNK_OPTION_ID,
1190     properties: {
1191         __not_really_there__: {
1192             type: 'number',
1193         },
1194     },
1195 };
1196 /** Recursive function that calculates the score of a `formData` against the given `schema`. The computation is fairly
1197  * simple. Initially the total score is 0. When `schema.properties` object exists, then all the `key/value` pairs within
1198  * the object are processed as follows after obtaining the formValue from `formData` using the `key`:
1199  * - If the `value` contains a `$ref`, `calculateIndexScore()` is called recursively with the formValue and the new
1200  *   schema that is the result of the ref in the schema being resolved and that sub-schema's resulting score is added to
1201  *   the total.
1202  * - If the `value` contains a `oneOf` and there is a formValue, then score based on the index returned from calling
1203  *   `getClosestMatchingOption()` of that oneOf.
1204  * - If the type of the `value` is 'object', `calculateIndexScore()` is called recursively with the formValue and the
1205  *   `value` itself as the sub-schema, and the score is added to the total.
1206  * - If the type of the `value` matches the guessed-type of the `formValue`, the score is incremented by 1, UNLESS the
1207  *   value has a `default` or `const`. In those case, if the `default` or `const` and the `formValue` match, the score
1208  *   is incremented by another 1 otherwise it is decremented by 1.
1209  *
1210  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used when necessary
1211  * @param rootSchema - The root JSON schema of the entire form
1212  * @param schema - The schema for which the score is being calculated
1213  * @param formData - The form data associated with the schema, used to calculate the score
1214  * @returns - The score a schema against the formData
1215  */
1216 function calculateIndexScore(validator, rootSchema, schema, formData = {}) {
1217     let totalScore = 0;
1218     if (schema) {
1219         if (isObject_default()(schema.properties)) {
1220             totalScore += reduce_default()(schema.properties, (score, value, key) => {
1221                 const formValue = get_default()(formData, key);
1222                 if (typeof value === 'boolean') {
1223                     return score;
1224                 }
1225                 if (has_default()(value, REF_KEY)) {
1226                     const newSchema = retrieveSchema(validator, value, rootSchema, formValue);
1227                     return score + calculateIndexScore(validator, rootSchema, newSchema, formValue || {});
1228                 }
1229                 if ((has_default()(value, ONE_OF_KEY) || has_default()(value, ANY_OF_KEY)) && formValue) {
1230                     const key = has_default()(value, ONE_OF_KEY) ? ONE_OF_KEY : ANY_OF_KEY;
1231                     const discriminator = getDiscriminatorFieldFromSchema(value);
1232                     return (score +
1233                         getClosestMatchingOption(validator, rootSchema, formValue, get_default()(value, key), -1, discriminator));
1234                 }
1235                 if (value.type === 'object') {
1236                     return score + calculateIndexScore(validator, rootSchema, value, formValue || {});
1237                 }
1238                 if (value.type === guessType(formValue)) {
1239                     // If the types match, then we bump the score by one
1240                     let newScore = score + 1;
1241                     if (value.default) {
1242                         // If the schema contains a readonly default value score the value that matches the default higher and
1243                         // any non-matching value lower
1244                         newScore += formValue === value.default ? 1 : -1;
1245                     }
1246                     else if (value.const) {
1247                         // If the schema contains a const value score the value that matches the default higher and
1248                         // any non-matching value lower
1249                         newScore += formValue === value.const ? 1 : -1;
1250                     }
1251                     // TODO eventually, deal with enums/arrays
1252                     return newScore;
1253                 }
1254                 return score;
1255             }, 0);
1256         }
1257         else if (isString_default()(schema.type) && schema.type === guessType(formData)) {
1258             totalScore += 1;
1259         }
1260     }
1261     return totalScore;
1262 }
1263 /** Determines which of the given `options` provided most closely matches the `formData`. Using
1264  * `getFirstMatchingOption()` to match two schemas that differ only by the readOnly, default or const value of a field
1265  * based on the `formData` and returns 0 when there is no match. Rather than passing in all the `options` at once to
1266  * this utility, instead an array of valid option indexes is created by iterating over the list of options, call
1267  * `getFirstMatchingOptions` with a list of one junk option and one good option, seeing if the good option is considered
1268  * matched.
1269  *
1270  * Once the list of valid indexes is created, if there is only one valid index, just return it. Otherwise, if there are
1271  * no valid indexes, then fill the valid indexes array with the indexes of all the options. Next, the index of the
1272  * option with the highest score is determined by iterating over the list of valid options, calling
1273  * `calculateIndexScore()` on each, comparing it against the current best score, and returning the index of the one that
1274  * eventually has the best score.
1275  *
1276  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used when necessary
1277  * @param rootSchema - The root JSON schema of the entire form
1278  * @param formData - The form data associated with the schema
1279  * @param options - The list of options that can be selected from
1280  * @param [selectedOption=-1] - The index of the currently selected option, defaulted to -1 if not specified
1281  * @param [discriminatorField] - The optional name of the field within the options object whose value is used to
1282  *          determine which option is selected
1283  * @returns - The index of the option that is the closest match to the `formData` or the `selectedOption` if no match
1284  */
1285 function getClosestMatchingOption(validator, rootSchema, formData, options, selectedOption = -1, discriminatorField) {
1286     // First resolve any refs in the options
1287     const resolvedOptions = options.map((option) => {
1288         return resolveAllReferences(option, rootSchema, []);
1289     });
1290     const simpleDiscriminatorMatch = getOptionMatchingSimpleDiscriminator(formData, options, discriminatorField);
1291     if (isNumber_default()(simpleDiscriminatorMatch)) {
1292         return simpleDiscriminatorMatch;
1293     }
1294     // Reduce the array of options down to a list of the indexes that are considered matching options
1295     const allValidIndexes = resolvedOptions.reduce((validList, option, index) => {
1296         const testOptions = [JUNK_OPTION, option];
1297         const match = getFirstMatchingOption(validator, formData, testOptions, rootSchema, discriminatorField);
1298         // The match is the real option, so add its index to list of valid indexes
1299         if (match === 1) {
1300             validList.push(index);
1301         }
1302         return validList;
1303     }, []);
1304     // There is only one valid index, so return it!
1305     if (allValidIndexes.length === 1) {
1306         return allValidIndexes[0];
1307     }
1308     if (!allValidIndexes.length) {
1309         // No indexes were valid, so we'll score all the options, add all the indexes
1310         times_default()(resolvedOptions.length, (i) => allValidIndexes.push(i));
1311     }
1312     const scoreCount = new Set();
1313     // Score all the options in the list of valid indexes and return the index with the best score
1314     const { bestIndex } = allValidIndexes.reduce((scoreData, index) => {
1315         const { bestScore } = scoreData;
1316         const option = resolvedOptions[index];
1317         const score = calculateIndexScore(validator, rootSchema, option, formData);
1318         scoreCount.add(score);
1319         if (score > bestScore) {
1320             return { bestIndex: index, bestScore: score };
1321         }
1322         return scoreData;
1323     }, { bestIndex: selectedOption, bestScore: 0 });
1324     // if all scores are the same go with selectedOption
1325     if (scoreCount.size === 1 && selectedOption >= 0) {
1326         return selectedOption;
1327     }
1328     return bestIndex;
1329 }

1346 /** Merges the `defaults` object of type `T` into the `formData` of type `T`
1347  *
1348  * When merging defaults and form data, we want to merge in this specific way:
1349  * - objects are deeply merged
1350  * - arrays are merged in such a way that:
1351  *   - when the array is set in form data, only array entries set in form data
1352  *     are deeply merged; additional entries from the defaults are ignored unless `mergeExtraArrayDefaults` is true, in
1353  *     which case the extras are appended onto the end of the form data
1354  *   - when the array is not set in form data, the default is copied over
1355  * - scalars are overwritten/set by form data
1356  *
1357  * @param [defaults] - The defaults to merge
1358  * @param [formData] - The form data into which the defaults will be merged
1359  * @param [mergeExtraArrayDefaults=false] - If true, any additional default array entries are appended onto the formData
1360  * @returns - The resulting merged form data with defaults
1361  */
1362 function mergeDefaultsWithFormData(defaults, formData, mergeExtraArrayDefaults = false) {
1363     if (Array.isArray(formData)) {
1364         const defaultsArray = Array.isArray(defaults) ? defaults : [];
1365         const mapped = formData.map((value, idx) => {
1366             if (defaultsArray[idx]) {
1367                 return mergeDefaultsWithFormData(defaultsArray[idx], value, mergeExtraArrayDefaults);
1368             }
1369             return value;
1370         });
1371         // Merge any extra defaults when mergeExtraArrayDefaults is true
1372         if (mergeExtraArrayDefaults && mapped.length < defaultsArray.length) {
1373             mapped.push(...defaultsArray.slice(mapped.length));
1374         }
1375         return mapped;
1376     }
1377     if (isObject(formData)) {
1378         const acc = Object.assign({}, defaults); // Prevent mutation of source object.
1379         return Object.keys(formData).reduce((acc, key) => {
1380             acc[key] = mergeDefaultsWithFormData(defaults ? get_default()(defaults, key) : {}, get_default()(formData, key), mergeExtraArrayDefaults);
1381             return acc;
1382         }, acc);
1383     }
1384     return formData;
1385 }
1386 //# sourceMappingURL=mergeDefaultsWithFormData.js.map

1389 /** Recursively merge deeply nested objects.
1390  *
1391  * @param obj1 - The first object to merge
1392  * @param obj2 - The second object to merge
1393  * @param [concatArrays=false] - Optional flag that, when true, will cause arrays to be concatenated. Use
1394  *          "preventDuplicates" to merge arrays in a manner that prevents any duplicate entries from being merged.
1395  *          NOTE: Uses shallow comparison for the duplicate checking.
1396  * @returns - A new object that is the merge of the two given objects
1397  */
1398 function mergeObjects(obj1, obj2, concatArrays = false) {
1399     return Object.keys(obj2).reduce((acc, key) => {
1400         const left = obj1 ? obj1[key] : {}, right = obj2[key];
1401         if (obj1 && key in obj1 && isObject(right)) {
1402             acc[key] = mergeObjects(left, right, concatArrays);
1403         }
1404         else if (concatArrays && Array.isArray(left) && Array.isArray(right)) {
1405             let toMerge = right;
1406             if (concatArrays === 'preventDuplicates') {
1407                 toMerge = right.reduce((result, value) => {
1408                     if (!left.includes(value)) {
1409                         result.push(value);
1410                     }
1411                     return result;
1412                 }, []);
1413             }
1414             acc[key] = left.concat(toMerge);
1415         }
1416         else {
1417             acc[key] = right;
1418         }
1419         return acc;
1420     }, Object.assign({}, obj1)); // Prevent mutation of source object.
1421 }

1438 /** Checks to see if the `schema` combination represents a select
1439  *
1440  * @param validator - An implementation of the `ValidatorType` interface that will be used when necessary
1441  * @param theSchema - The schema for which check for a select flag is desired
1442  * @param [rootSchema] - The root schema, used to primarily to look up `$ref`s
1443  * @returns - True if schema contains a select, otherwise false
1444  */
1445 function isSelect(validator, theSchema, rootSchema = {}) {
1446     const schema = retrieveSchema(validator, theSchema, rootSchema, undefined);
1447     const altSchemas = schema.oneOf || schema.anyOf;
1448     if (Array.isArray(schema.enum)) {
1449         return true;
1450     }
1451     if (Array.isArray(altSchemas)) {
1452         return altSchemas.every((altSchemas) => typeof altSchemas !== 'boolean' && isConstant(altSchemas));
1453     }
1454     return false;
1455 }

1488 /** Enum that indicates how `schema.additionalItems` should be handled by the `getInnerSchemaForArrayItem()` function.
1489  */
1490 var AdditionalItemsHandling;
1491 (function (AdditionalItemsHandling) {
1492     AdditionalItemsHandling[AdditionalItemsHandling["Ignore"] = 0] = "Ignore";
1493     AdditionalItemsHandling[AdditionalItemsHandling["Invert"] = 1] = "Invert";
